1)Class Name: University: Attributes: universityName,address, email, contact
Subclass Course Attributes: type(bachelors/masters..) ,name, length and fee.
Methods: getfees (check if fees is expensive)
2)Class Name Teacher: Attributes: firstName, surName, id,experience and salary Methods: salaryRange(if salary is good based on experience) training (If the experiene is below 2 years, then the teacher has to undergo a training)
3)Class Student: Attributes: firstName, surName, id, schoolScores and bankDetails Methods: previousScores (checks if the scores got in high school is good or average)

Courses select: [: x | x getfees = 'Expensive']. Courses select: [: x | x type = 'Masters'].
Students select: [: y | y previousScores = 'Average']. Students select: [: y | y surName = 'Gates'].
Teachers select: [: z | z salaryRange = 'Good']. Teachers select: [: z | z training = 'Training Needed'].
